snippet.textDisplay:
Bhagat Singh was a young revolutionary who sacrificed his life at a very young age fighting for the independence of mother India.

• He was born on 28th September 1907 at Banga village, Punjab rovince of British India) to Kisan Singh and Vidyavati.

⚫ He was a youngest fre fighter who was executed when he was only 23.

He got associated with the Hindustan Republican Association and formed Naujawan Bharat Sabha.

. He was involved in the murder of John Saunders in December 1928 to avenge the death of Lala Lajpat Rai.

• Bhagat Singh, Sukhdev, and Rajguru were hanged on 23rd March 1931, a day before the decided date.
